<div class="text-center">
    <h3>Update 1.4.0: Saved Encounters!</h3>
    <h4>5/21/2023</h4>
    <p>
        In the biggest update since release, you can now save up to 3 encounters! Instead of your original "Encounter" page, you have an "Encounters" page that lists your encounters. Your Creature Library, initiative list, each creature's HP, AC, and 
        notes will all be saved. If you aren't registered, now is a good time. You'll still have access to the original encounter page, but lose out saved encounters.
    </p>
    <p>
        Basic members get full access to this as usual! Premium members keep their usual perks, and help keep this site live and updates coming.
    </p>
    <p>
        This update also comes with some small quality of life perks. You can now take advantage of the "Smart Adder" in the Add Creature popup. When using the "Enter" key to add creatures to the initiative list, they will be added to the list as normal
        if they have an initiative value, but if the initiative value is empty, they'll be added to the Creature Library instead.
    </p>
</div>
<hr />

<div class="text-center">
    <h3>Update 1.3.0: Creature Library</h3>
    <h4>1/26/2023</h4>
    <p>
        Exciting update! In addition to some more memory and performance optimizations, when you add a creature like normal, that creature get's added to the Creature Library! That means, if you add 3 Goblins with 7 HP and 15 AC, and some special notes,
        you can open up the Creature Library and add more goblins, with the same HP, AC, and notes! The initiative input works just like you're used to, so you can add several more at a time.
    </p>
    <p>
        For Premium members, this also carries over the image you added, if you chose to do so.
    </p>
    <p>
        For Basic members, you still get full functionality of the Creature Library!
    </p>
</div>
<hr />

<div class="text-center">
